Env.Page.Title = Diagnosis

Env.Help.Text << EOM
In the <b>Telephony diagnosis</b> section, you can start various tests in order to check that the telephony system of your Box is correctly working.<br /><br />Just click on <i>Step 1</i> and follow the indications.<br /><br /><i>Initialization</i>: this test checks if the telephony configuration of your Box is correct.<br /><i>Equipment</i>: this test checks the electrical circuit used by the phone system.<br /><i>Ringtone</i>: this test checks that your Box can correctly make your phone ring.<br /><i>Dial tone</i>: this test checks that your Box can correctly communicate with your phone.<br /><i>Numbering</i>: this test checks the actions on the keys of your phone.
<br/><br/>In the <b>General diagnosis</b> section, by request of an SFR technician, you can export a diagnosis report that will be useful to the resolution of your complex technical problem.
<br/><br/>In the <b>xDSL modem diagnosis</b> section, you can proceed to an auto-test in order to check whether the xDSL modem of your Box is functional. Please check that the DSL cap is correctly plugged, otherwise the result won't be meaningful.
EOM

