Env.Button.Init = Start step 1
Env.Button.ReInit = Restart step 1
Env.Text.Init = This step checks that the telephony system of the Box is correctly initialized.

Env.Button.Gr909 = Start step 2
Env.Button.ReGr909 = Restart step 2
Env.Text.Gr909 = This step checks the electrical circuit used by the phone system. The Box may emit a noise due to the very specific load applied to the circuit. This is a normal behavior. Do not interact with your phone during the test.

Env.Button.Ring = Start step 3
Env.Button.ReRing = Restart step 3
Env.Text.Ring = This step checks that the Box can correctly make your phone ring.

Env.Button.Hookntone = Start step 4
Env.Button.ReHookntone = Restart step 4
Env.Text.Hookntone = This step checks that you can correctly hear the dial tone of your phone. Click on the button, then pick up the phone, listen for the dial tone, and finally hang up.

Env.Button.Dtmf = Start step 5
Env.Button.ReDtmf = Restart step 5
Env.Text.Dtmf = This step checks that the actions on the keys of your phone are correctly recognized by your Box. Click on the button, then pick up your handset receiver, press keys 0 to 9 successively in this order, and finally hang up.

Env.Button.CancelAndReboot = Cancel and reboot
Env.Text.Warning = Warning! You will have to reboot the Box after the diagnosis for the telephony to work again.
Env.Text.Info = The diagnosis will shut down all current phone calls.

Env.Section.dsltest.Title = xDSL modem diagnosis

Env.Text.dsltest_instruction = Plug in the test cap on the "DSL" port of your Box and click on the "Test" button. The test procedure will last for 20 seconds.
Env.Text.dsltest_living = DSL modem test processing

